== Overview ==
The Tenmon Hakase's duties included observing celestial phenomena (e.g., [[:en:Lunar eclipse|lunar eclipses]], [[:en:Comet|comets]], and other {{ill|astronomical events|ja|天文現象|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/astronomical events|qq=}}). If an anomaly was detected, the Tenmon Hakase would consult astronomical texts, interpret omens, and present a sealed report to the emperor in the {{ill|Tenmon Missō|ja|天文密奏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmon Missō|qq=}} ritual. The role also entailed instructing ten {{ill|Tenmonsei|ja|天文生|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmonsei|qq=}} students in astronomy. Notably, the Tenmonsei were forbidden to access astronomical texts, as specified under the {{ill|Miscellaneous Orders|ja|雑令|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miscellaneous Orders|qq=}}’s section on the prohibition of secret texts ({{ill|Hisogenzō|ja|秘書玄象条|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hisogenzō|qq=}}). Consequently, only the Tenmon Hakase and a few other authorized individuals could read these texts.

From the mid-[[:en:Heian period|Heian period]], following instruction from [[:en:Kamo no Yasunori|Kamo no Yasunori]], [[:en:Abe no Seimei|Abe no Seimei]] was appointed Tenmon Hakase. Thereafter, the position became hereditary, controlled by the {{ill|Abe clan (Onmyōdō)|ja|阿倍氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Abe clan (Onmyōdō)|qq=}} (specifically the {{ill|Tsuchimikado clan|lt=Tsuchimikado clan|lt=Tsuchimikado family|ja|土御門家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchimikado family|qq=}}).

